				<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/fa7795fb304f7316169fd3f7aff67ae4?s=48&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/fa7795fb304f7316169fd3f7aff67ae4?s=96&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' loading='lazy'/><span itemprop="name">rectorgroup LT</span> 			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-02-07T20:48:00-08:00" itemprop="datePublished"><a href="https://blog.sucuri.net/2010/04/conditional-redirects-or-the-htaccess-malware.html#comment-5253">February 7, 2012</a></time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p> Firstly download all infected ftp to your computer, with nodepad++ find all files with this &#8220;&lt;?php @error_reporting(0); if&quot;. thn delete them, after you will done it, delete malware from .htacces. Delete all your old ftp, and upload fixed ftp. Done 🙂</p>
		</div>

		
		
